Ratings of relational satisfaction and commitment from 282 (M)ixed-sex couples

Source: R/commitmentM-data.R
commitmentM.Rd

A data set containing 5 ratings of satisfaction and 5 ratings of commitment for each member of a mixed-sex romantic dyad. Measured using the Investment Model Scale subscales (Rubult, Martz, & Agnew, 1998). Data are from Sakaluk, Fisher, and Kilshaw's (in press) study of dyadic invariance. Variable names have been re-coded to follow a stem-item-partner ("sip") order, with a delimiter ("_") between the item number and partner distinguishing character.

data(commitmentM)

Format

A data frame with 282 rows and 20 variables:
